# CMakeLists.wasm.patch -- Blender CMake Compatibility Notes for WASM
#
# Status: NO PATCHES REQUIRED AT THIS TIME
#
# The current approach uses cmake/emscripten_overrides.cmake (loaded via
# -C flag) and cmake/wasm_sources.cmake to configure the WASM build
# without modifying Blender's own CMakeLists.txt.
#
# Key mechanisms that avoid patching:
#
#   1. -C flag loads emscripten_overrides.cmake as an initial cache file,
#      setting WASM compile/link flags before Blender's CMakeLists.txt runs.
#
#   2. WITH_HEADLESS=ON and 35 WITH_*=OFF flags disable features that
#      require platform-specific dependencies (GPU, audio, Python, etc.).
#
#   3. The custom entry point (source/wasm_headless_main.cc) is compiled
#      separately and linked via the build script, replacing creator.cc.
#
#   4. #ifdef __EMSCRIPTEN__ guards in the entry point handle any
#      platform-specific behavior.
#
# If future phases require changes to Blender's CMakeLists.txt (e.g., for
# GPU backend integration or Python support), patches will be added here
# with clear documentation of what they change and why.
#
# Prefer these alternatives over patching:
#   - CMake cache overrides (-D flags)
#   - #ifdef __EMSCRIPTEN__ guards in custom source files
#   - Wrapper scripts that adjust the build environment
#   - Separate CMake targets for WASM-specific components
